What you need to know:

NOC-K second vice president Waithaka Kioni, who is also the Chef de Mission for Team Kenya for the Tokyo Summer Games, indicated that the “bubble” training will in fact, be much safer with minimal movement in campThe camp that now has over 50 athletes and officials has been in operation for almost a monthThe athletics and taekwondo teams were joined in ‘bubble’ training by the sevens rugby teams Kenya Shujaa and Kenya Lionesses and the national volleyball team, Malkia Strikers